ADDITIONAL TERMS AND CONDITIONS FOR SAFEERASE

1. DATA DESTRUCTION DISCLAIMER
   This software is designed to permanently destroy data. The authors and 
   contributors are not responsible for any data loss resulting from the use 
   of this software. Users are solely responsible for ensuring they have 
   appropriate backups and are wiping the correct devices.

2. COMPLIANCE RESPONSIBILITY
   While this software implements industry-standard wiping algorithms and 
   generates compliance certificates, users are responsible for ensuring 
   compliance with applicable laws, regulations, and standards in their 
   jurisdiction. The authors make no warranty regarding legal compliance.

3. SECURITY LIMITATIONS
   No data destruction method can guarantee 100% unrecoverability of data. 
   The effectiveness of wiping depends on various factors including storage 
   technology, device condition, and implementation. Users should evaluate 
   the appropriateness of wiping methods for their specific security 
   requirements.

4. PROFESSIONAL USE
   This software is intended for professional use by qualified personnel. 
   Users should have appropriate knowledge of storage technologies and data 
   destruction procedures. Improper use may result in incomplete data 
   destruction or damage to equipment.

5. THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
